
# <type>[ (<scope>)]: <subject>


# <body>


# [<notes>]
#
# 50-character subject line
# 80-character wrapped longer description
# Sections wrapped in [] are optional, as noted below
#
# Allowed <type> values:
# * chore (updating ant/node/powershell tasks etc; no production code change)
# * docs (changes to the documentation)
# * feat (new feature for users in production code, not in a build script)
# * fix (bug fix for users in production code, not in a build script)
# * refactor (refactoring production code, eg. rewriting a function for clarity)
# * style (formatting, etc; no production code change)
# * test (adding missing tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
#
# The <scope> is optional only if the change is a global or difficult to assign
# to a single component.
#
# <body>: Use the third-person, present tense: "Changes X", not "Changed X" nor
# "Change X". If multiple changes are bundled, make sure to either space the
# lines correctly or prepend with a * to create a bullet-point list.
#
# Allowed <notes> types:
# * BREAKING CHANGE: Requires a description of the change.
# * Closes #nnnn: Double check to make sure you have the right issue noted, as
#    Gitlab closes issues automatically from commit messages.
